    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen displaying diagnostics using the `virtual_lines` handler, a new virtual line is created for the diagnostic no matter what. However, in some cases, the diagnostic text could fit on the line below without interfering with the text already on that line.\n\nExample:\n<img width=\"936\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f2385b5d-240c-4739-a67a-3eb94199ae20\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen the diagnostic could fit on the next line without overlapping with the existing text, it should do so, instead of always creating a new line.\n\nThe above example diagnostic could look like this instead:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/668f4718-485c-40a4-b4bc-913309eabb51)",
